-- Mauritius Caudan Development Heads for Lowest in Six Years
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-03-27T08:31:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/mauritius-caudan-development-heads-for-lowest-in-six-years.html
Caudan Development Ltd. (CAUDAN) , a
Mauritian company with interests in property, headed for its
lowest level in almost six years.  The  stock  retreated 4 percent, its biggest daily decline
since Sept. 20, to 1.20 rupee, by 12:15 p.m., in  Port Louis , the
capital. A close at this level will be its lowest since August
2006, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
